cs.CV, cs.CR, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.HC 

The paper deals with the use of deep neural networks for visual descriptors and content-based attributes of persons for assembling fair photo lineups. This suggests that the paper is likely to belong to the computer vision (cs.CV) and computer security and cryptography (cs.CR) sub-categories. Additionally, the use of recommender systems and preference learning indicates that the paper may also belong to the artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG) sub-categories. Finally, the involvement of forensic technicians in the evaluation of the proposed methods suggests that the paper may also belong to the human-computer interaction (cs.HC) sub-category.
